.SH NAME
Linux::Event::Reactor::Backend::Epoll \- epoll backend for Linux::Event::Reactor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&  # Usually constructed internally by Linux::Event::Reactor.
\&  my $backend = Linux::Event::Reactor::Backend::Epoll\->new;
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
\&\f(CW\*(C`Linux::Event::Reactor::Backend::Epoll\*(C'\fR is the built\-in readiness backend for
Linux::Event::Reactor. It translates the reactor bitmask into the event set
expected by Linux::Epoll and translates native epoll notifications back into
reactor masks.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new(%args)
.IX Subsection "new(%args)"
Recognized optional arguments:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`edge\*(C'\fR
.Sp
Enable edge\-triggered mode by default for all registrations.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`oneshot\*(C'\fR
.Sp
Enable one\-shot mode by default for all registrations.
.SH METHODS
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS name
.IX Subsection "name"
Returns \f(CW\*(C`epoll\*(C'\fR.
.ie n .SS "watch($fh, $mask, $cb, %opt)"
.el .SS "watch($fh, \f(CW$mask\fP, \f(CW$cb\fP, \f(CW%opt\fP)"
.IX Subsection "watch($fh, $mask, $cb, %opt)"
Register a filehandle with epoll and install the standardized reactor callback.
Returns the integer file descriptor.
.ie n .SS "modify($fh_or_fd, $mask, %opt)"
.el .SS "modify($fh_or_fd, \f(CW$mask\fP, \f(CW%opt\fP)"
.IX Subsection "modify($fh_or_fd, $mask, %opt)"
Modify an existing epoll registration. If the underlying \f(CW\*(C`Linux::Epoll\*(C'\fR
instance provides \f(CW\*(C`modify\*(C'\fR, it is used directly. Otherwise the backend falls
back to delete plus add.
.PP
This path is especially important for \f(CW\*(C`EPOLLONESHOT\*(C'\fR rearm.
.SS unwatch($fh_or_fd)
.IX Subsection "unwatch($fh_or_fd)"
Remove an existing registration.
.ie n .SS "run_once($loop, $timeout_s = undef)"
.el .SS "run_once($loop, \f(CW$timeout_s\fP = undef)"
.IX Subsection "run_once($loop, $timeout_s = undef)"
Call epoll wait once and dispatch readiness callbacks.
.SH NOTES
.IX Header "NOTES"
This backend keeps a small registration table keyed by file descriptor so it can
preserve callback, tag, and loop information across \f(CW\*(C`modify\*(C'\fR calls.
